d we not fix an appointment?' suggested Krug, rising from his chair and looking for his hat. 'I mean you might want some money in advance. Yes, I can see it. It is under the table. Thanks.'

'You are welcome,' said Quist. 'What about some day next week? Would Tuesday do? Around five in the afternoon?'

'That would be perfect.'

'Would you care to meet me on Neptune Bridge? Say, near the twentieth lamp-post?'

'Gladly.'

